Class OrderedStack<E extends Card>

  • java.lang.Object
    • OrderedStack<E>

  • public class OrderedStack<E extends Card>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a last-in-first-out stack of objects that extends Card. It represents a pile in the FreeCell game. This class is similiar to Stack class, but the push method follows the game rules.

    • Method Detail

      • push

        public void push(E cardInput)
          throws InvalidMoveException,
                 InvalidPileException
        Push an item onto the top of this orderedStack. These rules must be followed: 1. The suit of the card to be pushed and the suit of orderedStack must match 2. The face value of the card to be pushed must one point bigger than the card on the top of this orderedStack.
        Parameters:
        cardInput - the item to be pushed onto this orderedStack.
        Throws:
        InvalidMoveException - If the specified card is pushed onto without following the rules.
        InvalidPileException - If the specified card's suit does not match this OrderedStack's suit.
